reviewText: Story of British women in various WWII services.  Entertaining and a bit corny.  Nothing in depth or heavy.  An inexpensive addition to anyones war DVD collection.

Excellent WWII story of women in Britain participating in the effort.  Right on par with Millions Like Us.  Leslie Howard left a beautiful gift when he created this meaningful and sweet movie. Predicts emancipation for women after their participation in the war effort. Very good.
Wonderful! What more can I say!
Love these WWII propaganda films. They're so innocent in so many ways to our eyes.
